"You need to work."

22:57.600 --> 22:58.600
- You're throwing out
every reason

22:58.600 --> 23:00.400
you didn't want to get a job.

23:00.400 --> 23:02.333
Now, how does that
make me feel?

23:02.333 --> 23:03.600
[soft chuckle]

23:03.600 --> 23:05.734
If you don't want to do this,

23:05.734 --> 23:07.600
if I'm such a terrible person--

23:07.600 --> 23:09.467
- If I'm such
a terrible person!

23:09.467 --> 23:11.600
- Well...

23:11.600 --> 23:14.300
Maybe we should
just call it quits.

23:14.300 --> 23:18.300
♪ ♪

23:18.300 --> 23:20.333
- Coming up...

23:20.333 --> 23:22.467
- Why aren't you wearing
an undershirt?

23:22.467 --> 23:25.000
It's very strange.
Is it a laundry issue?

23:29.066 --> 23:29.266
[jazz music]

23:31.734 --> 23:33.600
♪ ♪

23:33.600 --> 23:34.633
- Here we go, buddy.

23:34.633 --> 23:39.033
♪ ♪

23:39.033 --> 23:41.100
- Hey, what's up, my man?
- You ready to go?

23:41.100 --> 23:42.767
- They asked me why I wanted
to get out of polo.

23:42.767 --> 23:44.367
Ask this guy.
He'll tell you.

23:44.367 --> 23:45.567
How many injuries have you got?

23:45.567 --> 23:47.633
- Hey, you only
go out two ways.

23:47.633 --> 23:49.100
Either dead or broke.

23:49.100 --> 23:51.100
- [laughs]
- And he's neither one.

23:51.100 --> 23:54.700
- I started playing
polo in 2005.

23:54.700 --> 23:56.633
It's a huge adrenaline rush,

23:56.633 --> 23:59.500
getting on
a 1,100 to 1,200-pound horse,

23:59.500 --> 24:01.300
normally a thoroughbred,

24:01.300 --> 24:03.367
you know, racing 30, 40 miles.

24:03.367 --> 24:04.633
I was talking
to Richard Stoney,

24:04.633 --> 24:06.367
he said,
"I've broken six bones."

24:06.367 --> 24:08.433
If I can get out without
having broken one bone...

24:08.433 --> 24:09.467
- Yeah.

24:09.467 --> 24:10.567
- I can't believe that

24:10.567 --> 24:11.633
the government still allows it

24:11.633 --> 24:13.367
to be legal, you know,

24:13.367 --> 24:15.133
'cause it's an
extremely dangerous sport.

24:17.400 --> 24:18.467
- Yeah.

24:18.467 --> 24:21.467
[cheerful music]

24:21.467 --> 24:22.467
♪ ♪

24:22.467 --> 24:24.633
- Oh, you look so good.

24:24.633 --> 24:26.100
♪ ♪

24:26.100 --> 24:27.667
That belt turned out perfect.

24:27.667 --> 24:29.467
- I love it.

24:29.467 --> 24:30.533
- Yeah, let me tighten it.

24:30.533 --> 24:32.000
Please do the red hat.

24:32.000 --> 24:33.667
- I'm so vanilla,
I'm chickening out.

24:33.667 --> 24:36.000
- I'm gonna make you.
- I don't know that I can.

24:36.000 --> 24:39.467
- You can pull it off.
- I'm going to bring both hats.

24:39.467 --> 24:41.667
- I'm so glad I stayed
over last night, and we, like,

24:41.667 --> 24:43.400
had this little sleepover.
- I know.

24:43.400 --> 24:45.000
- Today's like,
going to be really intense,

24:45.000 --> 24:46.066
I'm not gonna lie.

24:46.066 --> 24:47.400
- It is gonna be weird.

24:47.400 --> 24:49.000
- As much as I'm, like, removed

24:49.000 --> 24:52.133
from having feelings for Thomas,
like,

24:52.133 --> 24:56.333
just being at Brookland's gonna
bring back a lot of memories.

24:56.333 --> 24:59.567
In my head, I thought, "Oh
my gosh, this is the dream."

24:59.567 --> 25:01.166
It was gonna be
Thomas and Kathryn

25:01.166 --> 25:03.166
moving to a
beautiful plantation.

25:03.166 --> 25:04.734
I love you.

25:05.433 --> 25:07.033
- I love you.

25:07.033 --> 25:09.600
- It was literally
a figment of my imagination.

25:11.567 --> 25:14.433
- Oh, look at you, mama.

25:14.433 --> 25:16.500
- Do you like it?
- I love it!

25:16.500 --> 25:18.166
You are literally
the only person I know

25:18.166 --> 25:19.567
that could pull that off.

25:19.567 --> 25:21.433
- We should probably go.
It's like an hour drive.

25:21.433 --> 25:23.567
- I know.
All right.

25:23.567 --> 25:25.166
Let's do this.

25:25.166 --> 25:27.100
- Sh--,
they got everything here.

25:27.100 --> 25:29.033
[cheerful jazz music]

25:29.033 --> 25:30.667
- [whistles]

25:30.667 --> 25:32.567
♪ ♪

25:32.567 --> 25:36.433
Why aren't you watching
undershirts anymore?

25:36.433 --> 25:38.500
It's very strange.
Is it a laundry issue?

25:38.500 --> 25:40.467
- I don't know what shirt
to wear underneath.

25:40.467 --> 25:41.600
- A T-shirt!

25:41.600 --> 25:43.166
- There they are.
- Thomas!

25:43.166 --> 25:44.667
- What's up?
- What's up, man?

25:44.667 --> 25:46.533
[men chuckling]
- What's up, buddy?

25:46.533 --> 25:47.734
- Good to see you.
- You too.

25:47.734 --> 25:49.066
- Let's go get a drink.
- Right.

25:49.066 --> 25:50.200
- Is this the right way?
- Yeah.

25:50.200 --> 25:52.200
♪ ♪

25:52.200 --> 25:54.533
♪ ♪

25:54.533 --> 25:56.200
- Hola!
- Hello.

25:56.200 --> 25:57.600
Look at you in your fancy hat.
- Coma estas?

25:57.600 --> 26:00.200
- Muy bien!
[both chuckle]

26:00.200 --> 26:01.533
- You look great.
- How's it going?

26:01.533 --> 26:03.000
- Good to see you.
- Hey, Craig.

26:03.000 --> 26:04.200
You look good.
- Thanks.

26:04.200 --> 26:05.600
- Good, you look nice.

26:05.600 --> 26:07.200
- Hi, Austen.
- Hello.

26:07.200 --> 26:08.467
- You look good.
- How are you?

26:08.467 --> 26:09.533
So do you.
Look at this hat!

26:09.533 --> 26:11.467
Y'all so cute.

26:11.467 --> 26:14.200
Is this your derby attire?
- This is Naomi's.

26:14.200 --> 26:16.066
I had on something
completely different,

26:16.066 --> 26:17.667
and it ripped.
- Right in the pits.

26:17.667 --> 26:19.600
- So I didn't have Craig's
sewing machine,

26:19.600 --> 26:20.734
[laughter]

26:20.734 --> 26:22.100
- What you wearing on Thursday?

26:22.100 --> 26:23.066
- All white.

26:23.066 --> 26:24.433
- Are you excited for the--

26:24.433 --> 26:26.233
the ball or whatever?
- Yeah.

26:26.233 --> 26:28.100
- This is your
hot date over here?

26:28.100 --> 26:29.633
- Yeah.
- Well, better luck next time.

26:29.633 --> 26:31.767
- [laughing] Shut up.

26:31.767 --> 26:33.567
Who are you taking?

26:33.567 --> 26:36.500
- Kathryn.
- Yeah.

26:36.500 --> 26:39.767
- I heard you got an invite
to Patricia's little ball.

26:39.767 --> 26:42.233
- I did.
When I saw "Patricia Altschul,"

26:42.233 --> 26:43.767
I was like, "Oh, (BLEEP).

26:43.767 --> 26:46.100
Am I being served here?"

26:46.100 --> 26:48.500
- I'm not gonna take
credit for anything,

26:48.500 --> 26:51.633
but maybe Patricia's
starting to understand

26:51.633 --> 26:54.767
that Kathryn's not the same
Kathryn that she once knew.

26:54.767 --> 26:57.633
Kathryn took me to my surgery,

26:57.633 --> 27:00.500
and drove me home,
and brought me soup.

27:00.500 --> 27:02.500
[chuckles]
She's doing really well.

27:02.500 --> 27:03.600
- Yeah.

27:03.600 --> 27:05.000
- Hmm.

27:05.000 --> 27:07.000
- That warms my heart!

27:07.000 --> 27:08.667
- Isn't it nice?
- Yes!

27:08.667 --> 27:10.600
- Let's go, Thomas.
You ready to rock?

27:10.600 --> 27:12.100
- I'm ready to do it.

27:20.734 --> 27:22.633
- [sighs]

27:25.000 --> 27:26.266
- How you doing?

27:26.266 --> 27:27.700
You ready?

27:29.600 --> 27:31.600
[air horn blares]

27:31.600 --> 27:33.200
- To your right, to your right!

27:37.533 --> 27:39.667
- Oh, look at that.

27:39.667 --> 27:41.600
There goes Thomas.
He's about to score.

27:41.600 --> 27:44.133
I can totally tell
when a guy's gonna score.

27:44.133 --> 27:46.166
- [snickers]
Get out of here.

27:47.233 --> 27:48.266
- Yeah!

27:50.700 --> 27:52.500
- T-Rav!

27:52.500 --> 27:55.166
- What's up?

27:55.166 --> 27:57.033
- He'll acknowledge you;
he won't acknowledge me.

27:57.033 --> 27:58.633
- Hmm...
- Thomas and I just kind of

27:58.633 --> 28:00.033
pumped the brake a little bit.

28:00.033 --> 28:01.166
Lately,
I've just not been happy.

28:01.166 --> 28:02.700
- Okay.

28:02.700 --> 28:04.166
- And when
we get into arguments, I feel...

28:04.166 --> 28:05.166
Listen to why I'm always sick,

28:05.166 --> 28:06.266
and I have no voice.

28:06.266 --> 28:07.533
It's anxiety.

28:07.533 --> 28:09.633
Like, stress-related.

28:09.633 --> 28:11.567
Thomas is the only thing
I have over here.

28:11.567 --> 28:14.166
I feel alone and more isolated.
- Well...

28:14.166 --> 28:17.266
- I want a future, I don't want
to waste time on something--

28:17.266 --> 28:19.033
- Well, think about that.

28:19.033 --> 28:21.567
Definitely make sure--
- Would you date me?

28:21.567 --> 28:22.667
- Huh?
- Would you date me?

28:22.667 --> 28:24.567
If I break up with Thomas?

28:24.567 --> 28:26.133
[dramatic music]

28:26.133 --> 28:27.333
- [coughs]

28:27.333 --> 28:28.734
♪ ♪

28:28.734 --> 28:31.333
Well, I'm not a good safe bet.

28:31.333 --> 28:33.133
- Darn, I was like,
"Maybe there'd be a reason

28:33.133 --> 28:34.600
to stay in South Carolina."

28:34.600 --> 28:37.266
♪ ♪

28:37.266 --> 28:38.734
- Coming up...

28:38.734 --> 28:40.333
- You and Craig should go
together to the dance.

28:40.333 --> 28:42.066
'Cause we're getting
the band back!

28:42.066 --> 28:43.200
- Do you really want
to go together?

28:43.200 --> 28:45.233
♪ ♪

28:48.767 --> 28:49.200
[dramatic music]

28:52.333 --> 28:53.734
- I know everyone--I know
a couple of these dudes...

28:53.734 --> 28:55.600
- Are you running
out of booze up here?

28:55.600 --> 28:57.200
- That belt is Gucci!

28:57.200 --> 28:59.333
- Hey.
- Oh my gosh!

28:59.333 --> 29:01.600
- You look good. Look at you.
- Look at this!

29:01.600 --> 29:03.200
I should've put some
cowboy boots on.

29:03.200 --> 29:05.600
- Those are nice!
- No, these are--I like these.

29:09.200 --> 29:10.700
- Oh my God.

29:10.700 --> 29:12.367
[dramatic music]

29:12.367 --> 29:13.767
I remember this turn.

29:13.767 --> 29:15.367
Okay, now it's starting
to hit me

29:15.367 --> 29:18.100
now that we're getting
real, real close.

29:18.100 --> 29:19.633
♪ ♪

29:19.633 --> 29:21.233
Oh gosh, this is
gonna be interesting.

29:21.233 --> 29:22.300
[air horn blares]

29:22.300 --> 29:23.700
- Our halftime break--

29:23.700 --> 29:25.100
- Hey, we take
a ten-minute break.

29:25.100 --> 29:29.734
♪ ♪

29:29.734 --> 29:31.767
- You look really pretty.

29:31.767 --> 29:33.367
- Oh, God, this is gonna be...
- [laughs]

29:33.367 --> 29:34.467
[ominous music]

29:37.166 --> 29:38.767
- [grunts]

29:38.767 --> 29:40.367
♪ ♪

29:40.367 --> 29:42.166
- Hi.
- Hey, how are you doing?

29:42.166 --> 29:43.567
- Good, how are you?
- You look great!

29:43.567 --> 29:45.066
- Is the match over?

29:45.066 --> 29:47.033
- Huh? No, we got...
It's halftime.

29:47.033 --> 29:48.367
- Oh, okay. Nice.
- Hey, Danni.

29:48.367 --> 29:50.400
- We are winning.
We're undefeated thus far.

29:50.400 --> 29:51.767
- Thank you for having us.

29:51.767 --> 29:54.400
- Surely.

29:54.400 --> 29:55.400
- Wow.

29:55.400 --> 29:56.500
[scoffs]

29:59.734 --> 30:02.767
I remember walking these stairs
with Kensie in the car seat.

30:02.767 --> 30:05.000
♪ ♪

30:05.000 --> 30:06.667
- Deep breath.

30:06.667 --> 30:08.667
- You know, remembering
the smell of the barn,

30:08.667 --> 30:11.333
and how the screen door slammed.

30:11.333 --> 30:13.133
[screen door slams]

30:13.133 --> 30:16.734
It just has not
changed one bit.

30:16.734 --> 30:18.100
- Kathryn!
- Hello.

30:18.100 --> 30:19.734
- Hello, darling.
- Hello, everyone.

30:19.734 --> 30:22.000
- You look--I love it when
you just look like a badass.

30:22.000 --> 30:23.266
- Just crushes it.

30:23.266 --> 30:24.266
- You look insane.

30:24.266 --> 30:26.000
- Hi, I miss you.

30:28.266 --> 30:30.200
- So, this is the first
time I've been here

30:30.200 --> 30:32.033
since Thomas and I broke up.

30:32.033 --> 30:34.300
- Is it a good feeling,
or is it a sad feeling?

30:34.300 --> 30:37.033
- I don't know yet.

30:37.033 --> 30:38.433
- Yeah.
- Life is weird, man.

30:38.433 --> 30:41.033
- I know.
- Life is so weird.

30:41.033 --> 30:42.166
- So weird.

30:42.166 --> 30:43.200
[air horn blares]

30:46.300 --> 30:48.266
- Go, go, go, go, go!
- Come on, get around.

30:48.266 --> 30:50.033
- So you're watching
your man play a little polo?

30:50.033 --> 30:51.700
- He isn't scoring.

30:51.700 --> 30:53.033
- [grunts]

30:53.033 --> 30:54.700
- So how are you guys doing?

30:54.700 --> 30:56.700
- Oh, we're day-to-day.

30:56.700 --> 30:59.233
You know, we argue too much.

30:59.233 --> 31:02.033
Sometimes, I just feel like
I'm in the line of fire.

31:02.033 --> 31:03.400
And his dad, I talked
to him on the phone,

31:03.400 --> 31:05.166
and his dad always
says the same thing.

31:05.166 --> 31:07.033
"You're still here?"
- [soft chuckle] Oh.

31:07.033 --> 31:08.433
Well, we don't need you
joining the breakup bunch.

31:08.433 --> 31:09.700
- Yeah, exactly.
Exactly.

31:09.700 --> 31:12.166
- We need you
to keep it together.

31:12.166 --> 31:15.066
[bright classical music]

31:15.066 --> 31:17.734
- What's going on?
I mean, you look awesome.

31:17.734 --> 31:19.734
Look at this.
This is cool.

31:19.734 --> 31:22.000
- It's like Edwardian,
like, Victorian...

31:22.000 --> 31:24.066
- Yeah, yeah, it's like...
- That's what I was going for.

31:24.066 --> 31:26.066
- "Downton Abbey," or...
- "Downton Abbey."

31:26.066 --> 31:29.000
No, I'm just trying to
get pictures for insurance.

31:29.000 --> 31:30.000
I'm just kidding.

31:30.000 --> 31:32.467
- I have an idea.

31:32.467 --> 31:34.333
I'm gonna go with Austen.

31:34.333 --> 31:36.066
Shep and Kathryn
are going together.

31:36.066 --> 31:37.734
You and Craig should go
together to the dance,

31:37.734 --> 31:39.333
'cause we're
getting the band back!

31:39.333 --> 31:41.000
- She's not--she doesn't
want to go with me.

31:41.000 --> 31:42.467
- No!
- Relax!

31:42.467 --> 31:44.200
Everyone relax.

31:44.200 --> 31:46.400
- Ask me to go with you.
- Yeah.

31:46.400 --> 31:48.066
[dramatic music]

31:48.066 --> 31:49.400
- Do you really
want to go together?

31:49.400 --> 31:51.066
♪ ♪

31:51.066 --> 31:53.734
- I...
We have to talk about...

31:53.734 --> 31:56.233
- Oh, quit being such a p-word.

31:56.233 --> 31:57.767
- If I took her, it would mean
that

31:57.767 --> 31:59.767
we're making a step
towards getting back together.

31:59.767 --> 32:01.367
Oh, and then the next day,
what are we supposed to do?

32:01.367 --> 32:02.500
Act like--
- Be friends!

32:02.500 --> 32:03.767
- I guess you have a point.

32:03.767 --> 32:06.100
- He has a point.
- No.

32:06.100 --> 32:08.767
- This is such
an easy lie to avoid.

32:08.767 --> 32:10.367
Just say, "Naomi,

32:10.367 --> 32:12.233
I've invited somebody,
actually."

32:12.233 --> 32:14.033
- Well,
now I've broken the ice.

32:14.033 --> 32:15.300
I feel like my old self.

32:15.300 --> 32:17.500
I'm gonna bring her
to the winter ball.

32:17.500 --> 32:20.100
- You already invited her?

32:20.100 --> 32:22.367
- We're a little different
than you and Austen.

32:22.367 --> 32:24.033
- But you're not.

32:24.033 --> 32:25.767
- I thought I was
gonna marry Naomi.

32:25.767 --> 32:27.500
Did you think you were
gonna marry Austen?

32:29.367 --> 32:31.100
- I mean...

32:31.100 --> 32:32.767
- So I think we might be
in different boats.

32:32.767 --> 32:34.433
- [laughs]

32:34.433 --> 32:35.467
[air horn blares]

32:40.266 --> 32:41.533
- We should be clapping.

32:41.533 --> 32:42.500
- Oh, yeah.
- It's over.

32:42.500 --> 32:43.767
- Is it over?

32:43.767 --> 32:46.000
- Everybody's
so busy socializing!

32:46.000 --> 32:48.100
- Yeah, you're the
only one watching!

32:48.100 --> 32:50.533
- Now, that is some good polo!

32:50.533 --> 32:52.333
- We're going next door!

32:52.333 --> 32:54.133
Oysters, cocktails!

32:54.133 --> 32:56.000
- I like changes of venue.

32:56.000 --> 32:58.133
Change!
I do not fear change!

32:58.133 --> 33:01.133
[swinging jazz music]

33:01.133 --> 33:03.000
♪ ♪

33:03.000 --> 33:05.133
- This is like going back to
the scene of the crime.

33:05.133 --> 33:07.133
- I mean, this was your home.
- Thought of being happy...

33:07.133 --> 33:08.200
- You good?
You good, Kathryn?

33:08.200 --> 33:09.400
- No, I'm ----ing good,

33:09.400 --> 33:11.000
and it's weirding
me out a little bit.

33:11.000 --> 33:12.533
Honestly, I'm not even sad.

33:12.533 --> 33:14.333
I mean, this is, like,

33:14.333 --> 33:16.767
the only place where I felt
like I maybe had,

33:16.767 --> 33:19.033
like, a nuclear family
and a chance at one.

33:19.033 --> 33:20.567
So it's kind of
interesting being back,

33:20.567 --> 33:23.166
but it's fine at the same time.
I'm at peace with it.

33:23.166 --> 33:24.567
You know?

33:24.567 --> 33:26.166
- How's it going?
- [indistinct] Hello, Thomas.

33:26.166 --> 33:28.033
- Good to see you.
All right.

33:28.033 --> 33:31.100
- I never even thought I would
get over Thomas, to be honest.

33:31.100 --> 33:33.433
It's kind of like good
closure for me to see it.

33:33.433 --> 33:35.567
♪ ♪

33:35.567 --> 33:37.367
Oh my God,
this little fountain!

33:37.367 --> 33:40.033
This is where we
christened little Kensie.

33:40.033 --> 33:42.567
- It has really changed
my life, having Kensie.

33:42.567 --> 33:44.367
It's been
totally transformative.

33:44.367 --> 33:47.166
My lifestyle is, uh...

33:47.166 --> 33:49.367
Just take my word for it,
it's changed.

33:49.367 --> 33:51.166
[cheerful music]

33:51.166 --> 33:53.433
- I heard that this gumbo
is something to try.

33:53.433 --> 33:55.233
Nice.

33:55.233 --> 33:57.567
♪ ♪

33:57.567 --> 33:59.533
- No, that dude looks like--
- Chels!

33:59.533 --> 34:01.266
- Hey!

34:01.266 --> 34:03.066
- You should get some gumbo
and come join me!

34:03.066 --> 34:05.166
- Let me flirt a little longer.
I'll be right there!

34:05.166 --> 34:07.467
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
- [laughs]

34:07.467 --> 34:09.266
Who are you flirting with?
- Are you uncomfortable?

34:09.266 --> 34:10.266
- [laughs]
No, no, no.

34:10.266 --> 34:11.533
- Now, we're dating.

34:11.533 --> 34:14.333
[laughs]

34:14.333 --> 34:17.066
♪ ♪

34:17.066 --> 34:19.133
- I'm just trying
to be here all night.

